cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with multiuser beamforming and channel state information (CSI) acquisition in wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves networked systems and communication protocols, which are covered by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a new strategy for beamforming, which involves optimization and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The paper also involves signal processing and optimization, which are covered by cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy issues in wireless communication systems, which are covered by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
